Tags:
  - Beauty-Peace=Peace=The Tree of Emancipation
By: John Smith the Platonist
---
Religion though it hath its infancy, yet it hath no old age; while it is in its
minority, it is always in motu; but when it comes to its maturity and full age,
it will always be in quiete, it is then ‘always the same, and its years fail
not, but it shall endure for ever.’
